cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of face synthesis from visual attributes using deep generative models such as Conditional Variational Autoencoder (CVAE) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training and optimization of these models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of attributes to synthesize faces involves some level of artificial intelligence, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves image processing and manipulation, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of deep learning models for face synthesis involves some level of neural network engineering, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
